Morphology. Male (
Figs. 12 –17
, 42 and
47
). Measurements: Approximate body length: 14.0; head width: 4.5 ; thorax width: 5.4 ; forewing length: 10.8 . Coloration: Integument dark brown to black ( Figs. 12, 13 and
42
). Flagellum brown. Wing membranes yellowish, veins brown. Surface sculpture: Clypeus with smooth lower edge. Surface finely areolate with fine, sparse and relatively uniform punctation. Paraocular area with similar punctation, denser and coarser towards the vertex. Labrum irregularly punctate, with coarse and dense punctures intermixed (
Fig. 42
). Mesoscutum with fine and dense punctation, with some coarse and scattered punctures intermixed. Mesoscutellum areolate-rugose with coarse punctures posteriorly. Mesepisternum areolate-rugose with fine and dense punctures intermixed. Terga finely areolate with fine and dense punctation and with coarse and scattered punctures intermixed, coarser and denser on more posterior terga. Pubescence: Black with metallic bluish or greenish reflections on legs, sterna and posterior terga (
Fig. 13
). Head with dark brown to black hairs. Vertex, scape and clypeus with white, long and dense pubescence, mainly on the clypeus, extending past its lower margin (
Figs. 12
and
42
). Mesoscutum, mesoscutellum, area below the wings and ventral surface of the mesepisternum, pronotal lobe, tegula, mid- and hind trochanters, dorsal surface of T 1 and T 2 with white, long and dense hairs (
Fig. 13
), also present on T 3 -T 5 (although scattered) in some specimens. Structures: Mandible strongly curved apically with a short preapical tooth near the apex of the apical tooth (
Figs. 12
and
42
). Epistomal suture straight between anterior tentorial pits. Labrum relatively rectangular with the distal margin widely convex (
Fig. 42
); surface with a premarginal transverse concavity with other shorter and deeper depression at the lower margin forming two short rounded projections (
Fig. 42
). Area between lateral ocellus and eye flat (frontal view) (
Fig. 12
). Mesoscutum with a deep longitudinal median depression. Mesoscutellum with two poorly developed humps. Axilla slightly raised. Mid tibial spur with acute apex. Preapical tooth of claws with acute apex. T 7 bifurcate, apices rounded.

Female ( Figs. 10, 11 , 38 ,
45 and 46
). Measurements: Approximate body length: 15.1 ; head width: 4.4 ; thorax width: 5.5 ; forewing length: 11.7 . Coloration: Integument dark brown to black, flagellum brown (
Fig. 10
). Wing membranes yellowish brown with brown veins (
Fig. 11
). Surface sculpture: Clypeus finely areolate with smooth lower edge. Clypeus and paraocular area with fine, sparse and uniform punctation, denser and coarser towards the vertex. Surface of labrum irregular, with coarse and dense punctation mixed with fine punctures. Mesoscutum areolate-rugose with fine and dense punctation. Mesoscutellum with coarse punctation, finer posteriorly. Mesepisternum areolate-rugose with fine and dense punctures intermixed. Terga with very fine and dense punctation, with coarser and sparser punctures interspersed. Pubescence: Black with metallic bluish reflections on head, mesosoma and legs ( Figs. 10, 11 , 38 ,
45 and 46
). Clypeus with a longitudinal band of whitish pubescence on disc extended towards the supraclypeal area (
Fig. 10
). Postantennal area, vertex, mesoscutum, mesoscutellum, anterior surface of the tegula, T 1 and T 2 with whitish, long and dense pilosity (
Figs. 10 and 11
). Posterior edge of tibia and basitarsus of midleg with coarse, short and black hairs with curved apices. Pubescence of metasoma (except dorsal surface of T 1 and T 2 ) with green reflections, slightly bluish on sterna; all mixed with black, long, and simple hairs. Structures: Flabellum relatively elliptical. Mandible strongly curved apically with a short preapical tooth of acute apex (
Fig. 10
). Maxillary palpus with two palpomeres ( 2 nd> 1 st). Epistomal suture concave between anterior tentorial pits. Labrum relatively rectangular with convex lower margin; surface with a premarginal transverse concavity and other shorter and deeper depression at the lower margin forming two short rounded projections. Surface between lateral ocellus and compound eye flat (frontal view) (
Fig. 10
). Mesoscutum with a deep longitudinal median depression. Mesoscutellum with two poorly developed humps. Axilla slightly raised. Mid tibial spur with acute apex. Posterior distal edge of middle basitarsus with a spine-like projection. Claws with preapical tooth of acute apex, slightly truncate in the hind leg. Apex of the pygidial plate broadly rounded, only apically delimited.

